topic.title: NT MCG Capable Configuration Command

section.title:
PMCSJIRAJIRA-Q8530-449
Feature Description
section.draft-comment: This register can be controlled via Config Space and GAS so the MRPC command may not be needed. Can we make this topic INTERNAL and mark a FW limitation that the command will be removed (and the support in the driver would not be required)?
section.p: This command is used to configure NT Multicast Groups that are allowed to pass through an NT Endpoint to other partitions. It supports the configuration of multiple NT Endpoints in different partitions through a single MRPC call.
The "Partition ID Start" and "Partition ID End" can specify a partition scope in which NT Multicast Groups will be configured with the current command.

table.title: NT MCG Capable Configuration Command Return Values
MRPC NT MCG Capable Configuration Command Input Data

row.entry: Configure/Read NT MCG Capable Register in [“Partition ID Start”, “Partition ID End”). For example, If “Partition ID Start” is 0, and “Partition ID End” is 2, the NT MCG Capable Register will be configured to NT EP of partition 0 and 1, or will be read from them.

entry.p: Refer to description in “Partition ID Start”.
NT MCG Capable Register Low m
Low Dwords, only low 16 bits are valid. All other bits are reserved and will be neglected by firmware. Only available for write operation.
NT MCG Capable Register High m
High Dwords, All bits are reserved and will be neglected by firmware. Only available for write operation.
NT MCG Capable Register Low m+1

row.entry: Low Dwords, only low 16 bits are valid. All other bits are reserved and will be neglected by firmware. Only available for write operation.

entry.p: NT MCG Capable Register High m+1
High Dwords, All bits are reserved and will be neglected by firmware. Only available for write operation.

row.entry: Low Dwords, only low 16 bits are valid. All other bits are reserved and will be neglected by firmware. Only available for write operation.

entry.p: NT MCG Capable Register High n -1
